  "prompt": "On moon men feel lighter weight than earth?",
  "response": "Yes, that's correct! On the Moon, people would feel lighter than they do on Earth due to the Moon's lower gravitational pull. The Moon's gravity is about 1/6th that of Earth's. This means that if something weighs 180 pounds on Earth, it would weigh only about 30 pounds on the Moon. Consequently, a person would feel significantly lighter and could jump higher and move more easily in the lower gravitational environment of the Moon.",
